==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nomadize
<hw>Nom"ad*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Nomadized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Nomadizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To lead
the life of a nomad; to wander with flocks and herds for the sake of
finding pasturage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Vogules <qex>nomadize</qex> chiefly about the Rivers Irtish,
Obi, Kama, and Volga.</q> <rj><qau>W. Tooke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nomancy</ent>⟦br⟧
